    "narrative": "Woke from a vivid dream set in my grandmother's garden — the one she tended for forty years before she passed. I was helping her weed the tomatoes while she told stories about her own mother. The smell of dirt and sun-warmed leaves felt real. Three years since she died and I still reach for the phone to tell her things. Started journaling because she said writing keeps memories alive. Maybe this is how I talk to her now."
